# UB500 hardware testing (Phase 7)

Target: TP-Link UB500 (`idVendor=2357`, `idProduct=0604`, RTL8761BU, `rom_version=1` → `chip_id=2`).

## Agent: build on daas-dev, stage in fw_to_test/

NeoPC scp path (only):

```
/root/rtl8761bu-libre/fw_to_test/rtl8761bu_fw.bin
/root/rtl8761bu-libre/fw_to_test/rtl8761bu_config.bin
```

```bash
cd /root/rtl8761bu-libre/rtl8761bu-libre
docker build -t rtl8761bu-libre .
docker run --rm -v "$(pwd)":/work \
  -v /root/rtl8761bu-libre/rtl8761bu-non-free:/nf_ref:ro \
  -e NF_REF=/nf_ref/rtl8761bu_fw.bin \
  rtl8761bu-libre make <target>
.cursor/skills/ub500-hardware-test/scripts/promote-test.sh <profile>
```

**One target per message.** Give expected SHA256 of `fw_to_test/rtl8761bu_fw.bin`. User runs `try_new_firmware.sh` on NeoPC.

Bisect order: `test-nf` → `minimal-null` → `minimal` → `full`.

## User: NeoPC only

```bash
./try_new_firmware.sh   # scp fw_to_test/ → /lib/firmware/rtl_bt/, replug
```

Paste `journalctl` output. FC20 pass = no `fc20 tx timeout`. Vendor baseline = `fw version 0x09a98a6b`.

